HEADWORD: Hydrobromide
<hw>Hy`dro*bro"mide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound of hydrobromic acid with a base; -- distinguished from a
<xex>bromide</xex>, in which only the bromine unites with the
base.</def><-- analogous to hydrochloride or hydriodide -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

